## M15b.1 positive regression: bindings inside a value-position
## `if`-branch block are visible at use sites inside the same
## branch.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 post-impl review: pre-M15b.1, `synthBlock` did NOT
## enter the block scope created by `SymbolResolver.walkBlock` for
## value-position blocks (e.g., `if` / `match` expression arms
## that are multi-statement). The scope was created but never
## entered by `ExprChecker`, leaving every local binding inside
## the block lookup-invisible at its use sites. The bug was
## hidden because the silent-`unknown` fall-through allowed
## downstream type-checking to coast (and Zig's compiler caught
## anything that mattered).
##
## M15b.1 fixes the scope entry. This canary pins the supported
## shape: `if cond INDENT local: Type = ...; local + 1 OUTDENT`
## in a value position must type-check correctly with `local`
## resolving to its binding.

sub main()
  result = if 5 > 0
    doubled: Int = 5 * 2
    doubled + 1
  else
    0
  print(result)
